Elite Shooter Gating Rules
Single-Elite Constraint

At any time, only one EliteShooter may exist on screen

If an Elite Shooter is alive, no new Elite Shooter may spawn, even if kill thresholds are met

Elite Respawn Logic (Important)

When an Elite Shooter is destroyed:

Record the enemy kill count at the moment of death

The next Elite Shooter may spawn only after 30 additional enemies are destroyed

This rule applies regardless of the current total kill count

Example:

Elite dies at 67 kills

Next Elite may spawn at 97 kills

Not at 90, even though 90 is a multiple of 30

